  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies arguments for customizing a typeface clone, including variation axes, palette selection, and collection index.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a lightweight ref struct that groups the parameters needed
to request a specific variation of a typeface. Pass it to
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)> to create a new
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface> configured with the specified variation position,
palette, and font collection index.

Because `SKFontArguments` is a `ref struct`, it cannot be stored in fields,
arrays, or generic type parameters.

## Examples

```csharp
SKTypeface typeface = SKTypeface.FromFile("VariableFont.ttf");

// Clone with a custom weight axis position
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    VariationDesignPosition = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
    {
        new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate
        {
            Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"),
            Value = 700,
        },
    },
};

using SKTypeface bold = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
